Three travelers have died in an accident along the Lagos-Ibadan highway on Wednesday. The road crash reportedly occurred around 3:15 am at Mile 12 Market, Ogere axis of Ogun State. Three vehicles were involved, namely a Micra car with registration number BDJ257XF, a truck registered as T4916LA, and another truck with no registration number, Daily Post reports. Seven persons were involved in the crash, which includes one female adult. While three of the six men died, other passengers, including the female adult were rescued unhurt. The Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) confirmed the incident, saying the incident was caused by one of the trucks. The state FRSC spokesperson, Florence Okpe said who confirmed the incident said, “The suspected causes of the multiple crashes were excessive speed and dangerous driving on the part of one of the truck drivers who was trying to negotiate a turning point and the other truck coming from Ibadan with high speed rammed into the vehicle” Okpe disclosed that the corpses of the deceased victims had been deposited at the FOS, Ipara. -Advertisement- POLL She added that the crash obstructed the highway, leading to traffic diversion being managed by FRSC personnel, who are making efforts to remove the obstruction away from the road.